To convert a string to an integer usable by one of our public key ciphers,
--store the string in a file which will be the second command line argument,
  'input' in the following example: 
--type at the command line: ./convert txt input output
--output will hold the integer sequence

To convert the integer sequence back into the the original string 
--type at the command line: ./convert num output input1
--input1 will hold the original string
--if all went well, inpu1 will be the same as input 
